Classification: PUBLIC



Dear Geeta,



Kindly note without the requested documents we are unable to progress. We ask you to provide us the following document to review and a take the proper action: 



1.	Attached claim form duly completed in all respects(Both); 
2.	Estimation/Extent of loss to consider appointment of surveyor;
3.	Suppliers Invoice issued prior to loading, identifying the claimed items; 
4.	Receipt Summary (highlighting the claimed items);
5.	Copy of the AWB OR BL;
6.	Evidence of transit damage (Customs/Stevedores damage report/EIR);
7.	Clearing agent statement;
8.	Claim submitted to the responsible parties holding them liable and inviting them for a joint survey (include proof of sending / acknowledgement and reply, if received);
9.	Documents showing if the cargo was unloaded from container for customs inspection at the port;
10.	Appointment/ contact details/ location for a joint survey;
11.	Vessel arrival date, date of discharge from vessel; Date of customs inspection; Date/place damage noted;
12.	Photos of the cargos before and after loading showing the damages



Best 



